	{"commentary":"<h2>Movement Turn 21</h2><p>But we <i>can</i> attempt to prevent it from threatening our homeworld!</p><h3>Battle for Sector L5</h3><p>Thus, we have our first battle of the playthrough. We have 7 Cruisers (4 with Attack Level 1, 3 with Attack Level 2), versus the <a href=\"javascript:showBox('DM2')\">first</a> Doomsday Machine.</p><ol><li><b>Round 1</b>: Since this is its first battle, our first step is to roll for weakness. This DM rolls a 2 (weak to Fighters)</li><li>The DM has the Tactics advantage, so it gets to shoot first. Since our Cruisers' Attack ratings are uneven, the DM will prioritize the group with the highest Attack rating</li><li>The DM rolls 2,5,5,10 (3 hits) against our Cruiser Atk+2 group (7 - 1 = 6 to hit. We lost one Cruiser, and another got damaged</li><li>Our two surviving Cruisers (with Atk+2) will return fire (4 + 2 - 1 = 5 to hit). We roll 4,8 (1 hit). This reduced the DM HP to 6</li><li>Our four older Cruisers (with Atk+1) will fire also (4 + 1 - 1 = 4 to hit). We roll 1,2,3,10 (3 hits). This further reduced the DM HP to 3<br /><br /></li><li><b>Round 2</b>: The DM continues its pursuit against our Cruiser Atk+2 group, only there is not enough effective HP to necessarily use all the rolls. It rolled 1,5,8 (2 hits), followed by a 9 (miss). We lost a Cruiser, but the group is not quite dead</li><li>Our one surviving Cruiser Atk+2 returns fire. It rolled a 3 (hit). This reduced the DM HP to 2</li><li>Our Cruiser Atk+1 group rolled 4,4,6,9 (2 hits). This finished the Doomsday Machine off!</li></ol>",
