	{"commentary":"<h2>Movement Turn 27</h2><p>We <i>can</i> take advantage of Doomsday Machine tie breaker rules. Colonies at sectors I7 / H7 are both the same distance and the same size. The colony at sector I7 would put the DM closer to our homeworld, so that is its choice.</p><h3>Battle for Sector I7</h3><p>Since our eleven (11) Cruisers also happen to be at I7... a battle will take place <i>before</i> the <a href=\"javascript:showBox('DM4')\">second</a> DM gets a chance of destroying the planet.</p><ol><li><b>Round 1</b>: Since this is its first battle, it rolled a 4 for weakness (weak to Minelaying)</li><li>It will use its Tactics advantage to shoot first. Since our Cruisers are all the same, it simply rolls away (8 - 1 = 7 to hit): 3,4,5,9 (3 hits). We lost one cruiser, and another got damaged</li><li>Our ten (10) surviving Cruisers return fire (4 + 2 - 2 = 4 to hit). They rolled 1,1,3,4,5,5,6,7,8,9 (4 hits). The DM has been reduced to 4 HP<br /><br /></li><li><b>Round 2</b>: The DM gets to shoot again: 3,7,8,9 (2 hits). Another cruiser cleanly bites the dust</li><li>Our nine (9) surviving Cruisers shoot once more: 3,3,5,8,8,10,10,10,10 (2 hits). The DM has been reduced to 2 HP<br /><br /></li><li><b>Round 3</b>: The DM gets to shoot again: 4,5,5,10 (3 hits). Factoring in one previous damage, we lost two more cruisers</li><li>Our seven (7) surviving Cruisers shoot once more: 1,4,4,5,6,8,8 (3 hits). The DM has been finished off!</li></ol>",
